        "title": "fix(ci): cap ClawSweeper worker bursts",
        "body": "## Summary\n- lower the shared ClawSweeper worker budget from 128 to 64 and reduce background/repair/exact-review ceilings\n- reduce scheduled sweep fan-out and enforce an 8-slot durable exact-review queue\n- synchronize dashboard, workflow, docs, changelog, and capacity tests\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm run build`\n- `pnpm run build:repair` plus 563 repair tests passing\n- `pnpm run build:dashboard` plus 46 dashboard tests passing\n- `pnpm run check:limits`\n- `pnpm run format:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- branch autoreview clean\n\nThe change is intentionally conservative around GitHub secondary-rate-limit pressure: scheduled/repair lanes yield to priority work and the exact-review queue cannot exceed 8 concurrent leases.",
